{
  "text": "As the absence of ABCG1 may lead to an increase of ABCA1 protein expression in ABCG1 KO mice, [CITATION_1] we explored the possibility that the knockdown of ABCG1 activity could be compensated by upregulation of ABCA1 expression in our cell systems. However, analysis of ABCA1 protein levels in ABCG1 SKD THP-1 macrophages ( Figure 3F ) and in ABCG1 KD HMDM (supplemental Figure IIIA) indicated that ABCA1 protein expression was not significantly or consistently upregulated as a result of ABCG1 knockdown.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "26280946"
